Here and now.

1080
01:07:18,493 --> 01:07:21,656
If this is a tribal decision,

1081
01:07:21,663 --> 01:07:23,950
where is Yellow Hawk
and Little Bear?

1082
01:07:23,957 --> 01:07:26,824
Probably back home
sucking up your spit.

1083
01:07:26,834 --> 01:07:27,790
Billy.

1084
01:07:29,420 --> 01:07:32,754
I'm Lieutenant Governor Barnes.

1085
01:07:32,757 --> 01:07:35,089
This is George Shipley.

1086
01:07:35,093 --> 01:07:38,427
He's the president
of Stonehearst Mining Company.

1087
01:07:38,429 --> 01:07:40,090
This isn't Indian land.

1088
01:07:40,098 --> 01:07:43,762
After it was terminated we
purchased a leasehold on it.

1089
01:07:43,768 --> 01:07:45,759
My company holds
the rights to it

1090
01:07:45,770 --> 01:07:47,431
and these men are here
as my guests.

1091
01:07:48,606 --> 01:07:50,062
How many days
after the president

1092
01:07:50,275 --> 01:07:51,811
signed that termination bill

1093
01:07:51,818 --> 01:07:53,400
did your company get
your leasehold?

1094
01:07:55,029 --> 01:07:56,190
Oh, I can't, I can't remember.

1095
01:07:56,197 --> 01:07:57,779
I don't see that has
any bearing.

1096
01:07:58,032 --> 01:08:00,194
How many days?

1097
01:08:00,201 --> 01:08:02,784
The clay after termination
was signed.

1098
01:08:02,787 --> 01:08:05,119
And how much money did you
just happen to contribute

1099
01:08:05,123 --> 01:08:06,830
to the secret campaign fund?

1100
01:08:08,876 --> 01:08:12,119
$125,000.

1101
01:08:15,466 --> 01:08:17,048
What did you say
your name was?

1102
01:08:17,051 --> 01:08:18,667
My name is George Shipley.

1103
01:08:18,678 --> 01:08:21,010
I'm president of the
Stonehearst Mining Company.

1104
01:08:24,017 --> 01:08:26,054
You know, Shipley, I think
I'll just kill you

1105
01:08:26,060 --> 01:08:27,596
right where you stand.

1106
01:08:32,275 --> 01:08:34,482
We've made a terrible
mistake and you've

1107
01:08:34,485 --> 01:08:36,101
got the upper hand for now.

1108
01:08:36,571 --> 01:08:39,529
Take advantage of it and all
you'll do is fan the flames

1109
01:08:39,532 --> 01:08:40,693
of hatred higher.

1110
01:08:41,909 --> 01:08:47,621
And then later on, all of us
here, somehow, we'll get even.

1111
01:08:47,957 --> 01:08:50,494
Trying us isn't going
to solve anything.

1112
01:08:50,501 --> 01:08:53,038
Blue Elk?
Rolling Thunder?

1113
01:08:54,172 --> 01:08:56,834
I know we don't think much of
each other, but we're realists.

1114
01:08:56,841 --> 01:08:59,253
Now, what the lieutenant
governor has to say is true.

1115
01:08:59,260 --> 01:09:02,469
You may feel good now,
but you're gonna suffer later.

1116
01:09:04,641 --> 01:09:06,678
All right.

1117
01:09:06,684 --> 01:09:09,392
We'll not try you now.

1118
01:09:09,395 --> 01:09:12,854
We'll just take a good clean
picture of each and every one

1119
01:09:12,857 --> 01:09:14,313
of you for future reference.

1120
01:09:16,527 --> 01:09:17,688
Okay. You heard him.

1121
01:09:17,695 --> 01:09:18,730
I want two lines here.

1122
01:09:18,738 --> 01:09:21,025
Women to the front and men
to the rear.

1123
01:09:21,032 --> 01:09:24,696
And I want all the men to take
off them hats. Now.

1124
01:09:24,702 --> 01:09:27,444
Oh, you've really gone too far
this time, Billy.

1125
01:09:27,455 --> 01:09:30,072
You're making a terrible mistake
photographing those men.

1126
01:09:30,083 --> 01:09:32,541
You know, the last time one of
you Posners uttered

1127
01:09:32,543 --> 01:09:34,705
that lousy cliche,
one of you got killed.

1128
01:09:34,712 --> 01:09:36,248
Now tell me, don't you
ever learn?

1129
01:09:36,255 --> 01:09:38,622
You people back there.
That means you too.

1130
01:09:38,633 --> 01:09:39,714
Let's go.

1131
01:09:39,717 --> 01:09:41,958
And I'll swear to God you're
really gonna pay for this one.

1132
01:09:41,969 --> 01:09:44,711
Take that hat off.
I'm talking to you.

1133
01:09:44,722 --> 01:09:47,214
Jean, how much more is gonna
have to happen before you

1134
01:09:47,225 --> 01:09:50,343
get those kids to pull back
on those exposes?

1135
01:09:50,561 --> 01:09:54,099
Taking pictures of those people
just infuriated them.

1136
01:09:54,107 --> 01:09:56,724
It made matters much worse.

1137
01:09:56,734 --> 01:09:58,395
I know that, Carl.

1138
01:09:58,403 --> 01:10:00,394
But I can't tell the kids on
one hand I have

1139
01:10:00,405 --> 01:10:03,443
complete confidence that they
can govern themselves and then

1140
01:10:03,449 --> 01:10:05,565
on the other hand take it away
when there's an important

1141
01:10:05,576 --> 01:10:06,407
decision to be made.

1142
01:10:07,036 --> 01:10:09,448
Either you decide to trust them
on the vital decisions,

1143
01:10:09,455 --> 01:10:11,071
or you don't.
It's as simple as that.

1144
01:10:11,082 --> 01:10:13,244
Yes, but you can speak out,
can't you?

1145
01:10:13,251 --> 01:10:15,242
I mean get up and present
your point of view.

1146
01:10:15,253 --> 01:10:17,790
I don't see why you can't
argue against something

1147
01:10:17,797 --> 01:10:20,004
you think is bad
or destructive.

1148
01:10:20,007 --> 01:10:21,964
As long as the kids have
the right to vote it down

1149
01:10:21,968 --> 01:10:23,254
if they don't agree with you.

1150
01:10:23,261 --> 01:10:24,501
Yeah, I know.

1151
01:10:24,512 --> 01:10:27,129
But oftentimes kids have
a tendency to hero worship

1152
01:10:27,140 --> 01:10:29,598
and I just think if Billy
or I got up and argued a point

1153
01:10:29,600 --> 01:10:31,591
some of these kids
would just blindly follow

1154
01:10:31,602 --> 01:10:33,593
because they identify
with us so much.

1155
01:10:33,604 --> 01:10:36,266
And I'm sorry, I just don't
think that's fair.

1156
01:10:36,274 --> 01:10:39,141
What you're saying then is that
when you get right down to it,

1157
01:10:39,152 --> 01:10:40,938
you don't really believe they're
adult enough to make

1158
01:10:40,945 --> 01:10:42,561
their own decisions.

1159
01:10:46,451 --> 01:10:48,362
Grandfather,
I would be honored

1160
01:10:48,369 --> 01:10:49,780
if you would teach me

1161
01:10:49,787 --> 01:10:52,620
how to pierce the veil
and go to that other world

1162
01:10:52,623 --> 01:10:55,741
and make my own inward journey
to find my own center.

1163
01:10:59,130 --> 01:11:04,170
I would be honored, Grandfather,
if you would teach me the way.

1164
01:11:05,887 --> 01:11:09,846
You have many enemies in this
world waiting to destroy you.

1165
01:11:09,849 --> 01:11:12,307
If you are to survive,

1166
01:11:12,310 --> 01:11:16,144
you will have to find peace
in yourself first.

1167
01:11:16,147 --> 01:11:18,639
That is why I want to make
the inward journey.

1168
01:11:20,693 --> 01:11:23,230
The inward journey
is dangerous.

1169
01:11:23,237 --> 01:11:25,695
Filled with terrifying evil.

1170
01:11:25,698 --> 01:11:28,486
There are many demons
of great power.

1171
01:11:28,493 --> 01:11:31,281
It takes much wisdom to
learn that they are

1172
01:11:31,287 --> 01:11:32,823
of your own making.

1173
01:11:32,830 --> 01:11:36,164
And first, you must learn
to <i>see</i> your own shadow.

1174
01:11:36,167 --> 01:11:39,080
How will I learn to see
my shadow, Grandfather?

1175
01:11:39,754 --> 01:11:43,247
Many cannot survive
the dangerous inward journey.

1176
01:11:43,257 --> 01:11:47,000
But if you do, in time
you will come face to face

1177
01:11:47,011 --> 01:11:49,002
with your own shadow.

1178
01:11:49,013 --> 01:11:51,801
Then you will know
what I mean.

1179
01:12:00,399 --> 01:12:03,482
I think I see it, Grandfather.

1180
01:12:07,532 --> 01:12:10,240
Yes, I see it clearly now.

1181
01:12:10,243 --> 01:12:11,859
What color is it?

1182
01:12:16,958 --> 01:12:19,825
Blue. Bright blue.

1183
01:12:24,590 --> 01:12:28,458
That is a spirit looking
to see if you are worthy.

1184
01:12:28,469 --> 01:12:31,211
It takes many forms.

1185
01:12:31,222 --> 01:12:32,804
Where did it go?

1186
01:12:37,228 --> 01:12:40,391
When you can tell me
where the flame comes from,

1187
01:12:40,398 --> 01:12:44,266
I will tell you where it goes
when it goes out.

1188
01:12:58,207 --> 01:13:02,576
Grandfather, where will I look
for my shadow demon?

1189
01:13:02,587 --> 01:13:05,170
We think the spirits
live out there

1190
01:13:05,172 --> 01:13:08,085
but they and the shadow
demon live inside you.

1191
01:13:08,092 --> 01:13:11,630
He is all the evil in you
that others can see in you

1192
01:13:11,637 --> 01:13:13,298
but you cannot.

1193
01:13:13,306 --> 01:13:14,967
Why is that?

1194
01:13:14,974 --> 01:13:18,137
We all put forth an image that
we want other people

1195
01:13:18,144 --> 01:13:21,478
to think we are and that we'd
like to think we are,

1196
01:13:21,480 --> 01:13:24,097
but we all have the secret evil
side that is

1197
01:13:24,108 --> 01:13:25,940
painful to discover,

1198
01:13:25,943 --> 01:13:28,685
though others
can see it in us very easily.

1199
01:13:28,696 --> 01:13:31,939
How can I come to know
my evil side, Grandfather?

1200
01:13:31,949 --> 01:13:35,613
By the things in others
that make you angry.

1201
01:13:35,620 --> 01:13:39,113
Whenever you get upset
at someone or something,

1202
01:13:39,123 --> 01:13:42,115
it's because that quality that
you're upset about

1203
01:13:42,126 --> 01:13:43,958
really exists in you.

1204
01:13:44,128 --> 01:13:48,167
It is always easier to see
the evil in someone else

1205
01:13:48,174 --> 01:13:51,007
and by trying to change him,
think you are getting rid

1206
01:13:51,010 --> 01:13:54,219
of your own evil,
your own shadow.

1207
01:13:55,139 --> 01:13:58,632
It takes superhuman courage
to see that this fault

1208
01:13:58,643 --> 01:14:00,475
really exists in you.

1209
01:14:00,478 --> 01:14:04,142
That what you're really hating
and trying to change

1210
01:14:04,148 --> 01:14:06,856
is a quality of yourself.

1211
01:14:07,485 --> 01:14:10,477
Like the rugged man who hates
long-haired youth.

1212
01:14:10,488 --> 01:14:13,981
Underneath, he is secretly
afraid of his own femininity.

1213
01:14:13,991 --> 01:14:18,155
Grandfather, may I now descend
to the cave of the dead?

1214
01:14:18,162 --> 01:14:21,154
No, you are not yet ready.

1215
01:14:21,165 --> 01:14:23,497
First, you must seek
your own vision.

1216
01:14:23,501 --> 01:14:26,869
When your heart is open,
your vision will come.

1217
01:14:26,879 --> 01:14:30,167
And only after you've received
your vision will you have

1218
01:14:30,174 --> 01:14:34,384
some chance to survive
in the cave of the dead.

1219
01:14:43,688 --> 01:14:45,178
Hello, Blue Elk.

1220
01:14:45,189 --> 01:14:47,351
How long has Billy gone
without food and water?

1221
01:14:47,358 --> 01:14:49,019
<i>Seven</i> days now.

1222
01:14:49,026 --> 01:14:50,858
And on the eighth,
if he's worthy of it,

1223
01:14:50,861 --> 01:14:51,851
his vision will come.

1224
01:14:51,862 --> 01:14:53,853
But if a woman enters
these sacred grounds

1225
01:14:53,864 --> 01:14:55,275
the medicine is lost.

1226
01:14:55,282 --> 01:14:57,364
You'll have to go back,
I'm sorry.

1227
01:14:57,368 --> 01:14:58,574
What are you guys gonna do when

1228
01:14:58,577 --> 01:15:00,033
the women's lib
hears about this?

1229
01:15:00,037 --> 01:15:02,074
You'll have to take that
up with the spirits.

1230
01:15:18,806 --> 01:15:21,343
Come, Billy Jack. Come.

1231
01:15:22,226 --> 01:15:23,716
For I am going to show you

1232
01:15:23,728 --> 01:15:25,890
the true nature
of the white man

1233
01:15:25,896 --> 01:15:27,432
through all of history.

1234
01:15:28,107 --> 01:15:30,519
Come and look with me
over this river of time.

1235
01:15:31,318 --> 01:15:32,353
Look out.

1236
01:15:33,195 --> 01:15:35,562
There's St. Augustine,

1237
01:15:35,573 --> 01:15:39,737
preaching the Christian creed
of love to the Druid Britons,

1238
01:15:39,744 --> 01:15:43,237
with the tips of their lances
dripping with blood.

1239
01:15:43,998 --> 01:15:47,787
Oh, and there's King Richard
the Lionhearted,

1240
01:15:47,793 --> 01:15:51,331
slaughtering the heathen until
